briefdescription.para: A standard code, or a local value from a custom coding system, that can be used to consistently identify, or provide a standard value for, the coded item.
The human readable text that accompanies the assigned code and represents the code's precise meaning (semantics) or usage.
Degree of match between the mapped item and the assigned code - holds an entry from an enumerated list of match types.
NEW: Web resource that provides information about the code

Data type enumeration derived from W3C XML Schema. If the code is derived from a local value system (e.g., numbered answer choices such as clock positions, tumor grades, or clinical scoring systems), then the data type of the local value may be specified here. This may be important if the code value will need to me manipulated mathematically.
